<div class="mb-requirement-container">
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-2559">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 1. </span>
      Explain to your counselor the precautions that must be followed for the
      safe use and operation of a sculptor's tools, equipment, and other
      materials. <br /><br />Resources:<br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/-fX0YeZnEME?si=suWmdxmEVZaWz3L2" target="_blank"
        >Working Safely With Clay &amp; DIY Modeling Tools (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a
        href="https://artabys.com/the-essential-rules-of-clay-safety-what-you-need-to-know/"
        target="_blank"
        >The Essential Rules of Clay Safety: What You Need To Know (website)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-2560">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 2. </span>
      Do TWO of the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-2560 mb-requirement-id-2561">
        (a) Model in clay a life-size human head. Then sculpt in modeling clay,
        carve in wood or plaster, or use 3D modeling software to make a
        small-scale model of an animal or person. Explain to your counselor the
        method and tools you used to sculpt the figure.
        <br /><br />Resources:<br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/6dnyYu4Ff7U?si=j9qg_lNcXGVH7HnQ"
          target="_blank"
          >Sculpting a Head in Clay (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/G-Drvb5WTM0?si=PbFCpiwrwnoTyGOl"
          target="_blank"
          >Portrait Sculpting in Clay (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/IyBRSsVQOTY?si=w4VRR1chFY0pE7ns"
          target="_blank"
          >Clay Sculpting Tools (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-2560 mb-requirement-id-2563">
        (b) Make a plaster mold of a fruit or vegetable. In this mold, make a
        copy of the fruit or vegetable. Explain to your counselor the method and
        tools you used to make the copy. <br /><br />Resources:<br />
        <a
          href="https://www.instructables.com/Fruit-and-Vegetable-Art-Silicone-Moulds-and-Plaste/"
          target="_blank"
          >Fruit and Vegetable Art - Silicone Moulds and Plaster Casts
          (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/FN7WLH5tNaY?si=mxbwZBRnf3lv6s6f"
          target="_blank"
          >Plaster Fruit Cast (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-2560 mb-requirement-id-2564">
        (c) With your parent or guardian's permission and your counselor's
        approval, visit a museum, art exhibit, art gallery, artists' co-op, or
        artist's studio. After your visit, share with your counselor what you
        have learned. Discuss the importance of visual arts and how it
        strengthens social tolerance and helps stimulate cultural, intellectual,
        and personal development. <br /><br />Resource:<br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/drrBd1bCiW0?si=K3DwDeSzVPwmYDyy"
          target="_blank"
          >How To Visit an Art Museum (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-2566">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 3. </span>
      Find out about career opportunities in sculpture. Pick one and find out
      the education, training, and experience required for this profession.
      Discuss this with your counselor, and explain why this profession might
      interest you. <br /><br />Resources:<br />
      <a
        href="https://www.indeed.com/career-advice/finding-a-job/careers-for-sculptors"
        target="_blank"
        >12 Careers for Sculptors (website)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/N6HeVopwRmQ?si=YJyPrJ4CvPLj9cx0" target="_blank"
        >How To Become an Artist/Sculptor (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/T_X9ZdUq-2Q?si=p0lV3ApJiQH0OqXe" target="_blank"
        >Craft Artist Careers (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
